irubin elevation greater than 2 times ULN, aminotransferase elevations are greater than 8 times ULN, or aminotransferase elevations persist beyond 2 weeks.', 'Synergism', 'The use of bedaquiline with other potentially hepatotoxic agents should be avoided whenever possible (e.', 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/7824/', '', 'Omadacycline, Eravacycline, Demeclocycline, Sarecycline, Tigecycline, Acetylsalicylic acid, Amphotericin B, Miconazole, Hydrocortisone, Prednisolone, Triamcinolone, More', 'Capreomycin, Pyrazinamide, Rifamycin, Sulfamethoxazole, Rifapentine, Cycloserine, Ethambutol, Pyridoxine, Ethionamide, Pretomanid, Aminosalicylic acid', 1767369485);
